Replies such as the one you have just given to me are usually done to be so vague as to make it seem as if you have something extremly deep and thoughtful behind your words, when in fact, you're saying nothing but trying to look smart doing it.  Your first responce speaks of the game as it could be played on any server and makes no special mention of FV or its ruleset which instantly disqualifies it from having anything resembling a point to anything I, or anyone else, had to say.  Your second is just mind-numbing fluff.  To put it plainly, you're trying to flame me and doing a horrible job.<br>
<br>
FV was created for RPers.  Period.  I am not an RP Nazi, but I am against people coming to FV with no intention of playing a character. The great thing about how the server stands now is that basically everyone is friendly.  People seem to want to be here to enjoy the atmosphere of family and fun.  One of the things I love so much is that loot is not a concern.<br>
<br>
So let me make this clear from my standpoint.  I do not care about uber-loot or the distribution of it.  I do not care if I re-roll and meet up with a level 5 warrior in full ToV gear, so long as he is adding to the positive atmosphere by being a character.  I do however care about lame-ass, wanna-be power-gamers coming into FV because they can finally be king of the hill, if only because the real powergamers wouldn't waste their time coming here.  Who wants to be king of the anthill?<br>
<br>
Selling &quot;uber-loot&quot; will not be the cause of FVs decline.  It seems to me most of the people who are getting upset are those who already HAVE uber-gear.  The cry &quot;They didn't earn it&quot; looks like &quot;It's not fair because now everyone will be as uber as me and I had to 'work' really hard for mine&quot; because of the attitude behind all the posts.  The respect for a character on FV does not, in my opinion, seem to be based on ones equipment AT ALL!!  Who watches Mr Uber-guild-member_02 run by in the Nexus and go &quot;Wow, he's so cool!  He has PoH armor!!!  I want to just as cool as him!&quot;  Such thinking is for blue servers.<br>
<br>
What would be bad is a flood of d00ds coming over for no reason other than so they can get buy the great no-drop loot here.  Coming to FV to abuse the unique rules = bad.<br>
<br>
But I don't see that happening, as someone who has that much of a desire for loot will be playing on a server that CARES about loot... not FV.  It's not too hard to pop on a blue server, play 24 hours a day, and find your way into an uber-guild.  No need to come here and buy it.  As I said, king of the anthill.  So what I see as being both plausable and bad is the people who just can't hack it on blues coming over here.<br>
<br>
