<br>
So, our people ported in, plenty enough to kill Lodi. Did DA have enough to kill him then? I don't know, possibly, possibly not, that is one of those unanswerable questions. Note that I was not there for this one, I heard on guild chat, and it seemed to me that in the intertests of future good will we should just let them have it, even tho we had spotted it first and arrived with the force to kill him possibly first as well. But the people there were like 'We saw him first, we got the force here to kill him first, why should we let him go, we all just left our camps, blah blah'. However, after some convincing on my part and on the part of others, and because the mistake was certainly an understandable one, we gave them the loot.<br>
<br>
And how exactly, then, was this a dishonorable act? We saw him first, we quite possibly had the force to kill him there first, and even though we did kill him, we gave them the loot, no prob. Seems like we acted extraordinarily fairly here, all things considered. But I guess everyone has their own point of view.<br>
