 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwitherweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/7/02 7:36:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=489.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: well, there goes the neighborhood</span><hr size=1> (In response to Alyissa's post)<br>
<br>
I came to FV because I was sick of all the shouting, babbling, oneup-manship, and other blabber on the other servers.  PvP servers are filled with people who get off on feeling bigger because they're twink is greater than your twink.  Blue servers are too populated and full of beggers, shouters, trainers, etc.<br>
<br>
FV is nice and peaceful.  The main thing that convinced me to join here was no zone-wide shouts and no auctions in non city zones.  That alone makes this server far superior to any other server.  In addition, I figured people that liked to role-play were, on the average, more friendly and intelligent then the average monkey.. I mean, &quot;d00d players&quot; on the other servers.<br>
<br>
I also want to play the high end game, because I find that that's the enjoyable part of the game.  If I was truly a dark elf wizard, then I wouldn't have fun chatting with people or going to weddings or consipring on how to take out Another_Useless_Highelf_00.  I'd want to blow stuff up.  Like dragons and giants and big scary monsters.  So, that's what I do.  <br>
<br>
I joined Fire and Fury because we take out big stuff, and I like doing that.  <br>
<br>
(I was intending to tie this to your post somehow..)<br>
<br>
What I also like here is that I don't see every level 5 player running around in level 50+ armor.  In my opinion that trivializes the game.  It annoyed me on Tallon Zek when every single player you ran in to had gear that dropped in level 50+ zones and had an MR of 200+ and killed you in 2 seconds.  It became pointless to do anything when you'd always just run into a twink that could take you down easily.  On (established) blue servers, the market is so saturated that your standard level 1 bard is running around in full lambent or singing steel, your standard level 1 warrior has a lammy and a wurmslayer, etc etc.  I think that trivializes the game.  It doesn't kill my enjoyment of it, but it lessens the enjoyment for me some.<br>
<br>
I'm not speaking for the others in Fire and Fury who are debating the topic of loot and such, but I think I can understand where they're coming from.  <br>
<br>
Anyway I didn't come here to be king of anything, let alone an anthill.  I don't dislike the idea of distribution of planar gear becuase I won't look as good in comparison to others.  I don't like the idea of distribution of planar gear to those who can't go to planes because it would make this server about the same as the other servers I've been on.  The arguments that others in Fire and Fury are making is that people who buy planar gear aren't earning their equipment.  If everyone can go shell out a few thousand plat (which is trivial to get) to buy planar armor, there's no real point for the level 46 restriction to go there.  You just let your Local_Uber_Guild_00 go there and wait for them to flood the marketplace.<br>
<br>
Witherweaver<br>
59 Dark Elf Wizard<br>
Fire and Fury<br>
