<br>
Galtron walks into the bar with a grim face and orders an ale.  <br>
A novice adventurer looks upon Galtron and whispers to his friend: &quot;By Tunare!  That is the great warrior Galtron.  And look at that breastplate he has donned.  It is rumored he had to kill the great Dragon Trakenon himself for such a prize!  And that sword.  Rumor has it that it was wielded by a horrid snakeman in the Temple of Ssraeshza, the legendary enslavers of the Iksar race.  This is a powerful and great man indeed, my friend&quot;<br>
<br>
(by the way I made up the name &quot;Galtron&quot; so I'm not referring to anyone, and I'm not trying to imply that Trakanon or Ssra mobs are &quot;uber&quot; or anything)<br>
<br>
You have to take that with a grain of salt, but you have to take all of Everquest with a grain of salt if you're trying to roleplay.  <br>
<br>
At any rate, if I was roleplaying in D&amp;D and I was a level 3 warrior in leather armor with a long sword, and then a warrior walked in with plate armor, some ornate shield, a fiery sword, etc I'd automatically give him a little respect and awe.  I'd look at my crappy long sword with dried orc blood on it and think: &quot;Someday I will be a champion of the realms like he is&quot;.   Or if I was a wizard and cast detect magic and a robed figure lit up like a Christmas tree -)<br>
<br>
Witherweaver<br>
59 Wizard<br>
